<TITLE> Sports awards to be distributed on June 21 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 12 (bdnews24.com) - The National Sports Award will be distributed on June 21 at Osmani Memorial Auditorium in city. Chief Adviser to Caretaker Government Dr Fakhruddin Ahmed is expected to distribute the awards among the winners. The awards include gold medals, certificates and Tk 20,000 to each awardee. Ten sports personalities will be awarded, a press release said.. The names of awardees are M Hasanuzzaman Bablu and Khandokar Wasim Iqbal (football), Mohammad Rafique (cricket), Sharmin Akhter (shooting), M Ehtesham Sultan (hockey), Fouzia Huda Jui (athletics), Mahmuda Sharif (swimming), Azad Abul Kalam (body building and weightlifting), Nayana Chowdhury (judo) and lieutenant colonel (rtd) MA Hamid (organiser). Some 158 sportspersons received national sports awards in 29 years from 1976 to 2005. 
